# Rust Conventions

## Module Structure

```
src/
├── lib.rs           — Tauri app setup, state management, event dispatch
├── main.rs          — Entry point (Tauri bootstrap)
├── engine/          — Input processing pipeline
│   ├── kalman.rs    — 2D Kalman filter (state: [x, y, vx, vy])
│   ├── accel.rs     — Acceleration curves (Linear/Quadratic/S-curve)
│   ├── trackball.rs — Trackball physics (fling + friction decay)
│   └── gestures.rs  — Gesture type definitions
├── protocol/        — TBP wire format
│   ├── packets.rs   — Header/payload encode/decode (bincode v2)
│   └── crypto.rs    — AES-128-GCM, X25519 ECDH, HKDF key derivation
├── server/          — Network layer
│   ├── udp.rs       — Tokio UDP server on port 47474
│   ├── connection.rs— Session state machine (handshaking→connected→timeout)
│   └── mdns.rs      — mDNS service registration via mdns-sd
├── injector/        — Platform input injection
│   ├── platform.rs  — InputInjector trait + InjectorError
│   ├── macos.rs     — CGEvent-based injection (requires Accessibility)
│   ├── windows.rs   — SendInput-based injection
│   └── linux.rs     — Stub/placeholder
└── settings/        — Configuration persistence
    ├── config.rs    — AppConfig serde + file I/O
    └── profiles.rs  — Built-in profiles (Precise/Default/Fast/Linear)
```

## Rules

- Run `cargo fmt` before committing; CI enforces `cargo fmt --check`
- Run `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` — zero warnings policy in CI
- Run `cargo test --all-features` — includes proptest round-trip tests
- Use `anyhow::Result` for fallible functions; `thiserror` for domain error enums
- Serialization: `bincode v2` (RC) with fixed-int encoding for protocol; `serde_json` for config
- Async runtime: `tokio` with `features = ["full"]`
- Feature flag `testing` enables `proptest` in library code
- Performance: keep the hot path (Touch → Kalman → inject) allocation-free
- All `#[cfg(target_os)]` code lives in the `injector/` submodules; never put platform-specific code elsewhere
- Config file path: macOS `~/Library/Application Support/TrackBallWatch/config.json`, Windows `%APPDATA%\TrackBallWatch\config.json`
